{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Executes the activation event associated with the calling object. The nature of the activation event depends on the object type and two optional flags. |name = Activate |returnType = void |referenceType = [Object] |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = ActionRef |Type = ref |Optional = y }}{{FunctionArgument |Name = RunOnActivateBlockFlag |Type = int |Value = 0, 1 |Optional = y }} |example = Activate Player ContainerRef.Activate ActivatorRef.Activate Player 1 }}
==Parameters== {| {{Wikitable}} |- !Parameter !Value !Result |- |''ActionRef'' |unspecified |The calling reference's ''ActionRef'' will be used. If the calling reference doesn't have an ''ActionRef'', the object won't be activated. |- |''ActionRef'' |specified |Sets the ''ActionRef'' for the function call. Useful if you use [[IsActionRef]] or [[GetActionRef]] inside of the [[OnActivate]] block of the object. |- |''RunOnActivateBlockFlag'' |0 or unspecified |The object will perform its default activation, bypassing any [[OnActivate]] Block in its script. |- |''RunOnActivateBlockFlag'' |1 |The [[OnActivate]] block of the object will be run ''instead'' of the default activation. ''(Note, you must specify an ActionRef in this case)'' |} {{break}}
==Default Activation== If the Player is the ''ActionRef'': {| {{Wikitable|style=width:20%}} |- !Object Type !Activation |- |NPC |Dialogue |- |Container |Opens |- |Door |Opens |- |Weapon, armor, etc |Picks Up |}
==Notes== *Note that 'Activate Player' does NOT activate the player. It activates the calling reference and sets the player as the ''ActionRef'' (the reference that activated it). *There are a number of peculiarities and bugs with the '''Activate''' function: #For [[Enable]]d NPCs, activating an item will force them to pick it up (even if they're [[SetUnconscious|unconscious]]). However, containers won't pick up the item. #When you use the ''RunOnActivateBlockFlag'', the script of the activated object will run immediately, meaning the next line of the activating references's script won't be processed until the entire script (including blocks other than [[OnActivate]]) finishes. If the activated script doesn't have an [[OnActivate]] block, it won't run. #Calling '''Activate''' with the ''RunOnActivateBlockFlag'' set to 0 on an object which doesn't have an [[OnActivate]] block in its script, or has no script at all, will prevent that object from being activated normally ever again. For example, if '''Activate''' is called on an unscripted container, the player will no longer be able to open that container by activating it; similarly, calling '''Activate''' on unscripted NPCs prevents the player from being able to talk to them. Therefore, use ''RunOnActivateBlockFlag'' = 0 only if you know for sure the object has an [[OnActivate]] block and, for some reason, you don't want that code to run. #You can use 'Activate Player 1', while an item is in an inventory, to have it run its own [[OnActivate]] block. However, you have to place the [[OnActivate]] block on the top of the script. #If you add a [[Message|MessageBox]] to the [[OnActivate]] block of a container and then issue the '''Activate''' command somewhere after the call to the [[Message|MessageBox]], the in-game result will be an opened inventory dialog box of the container with a [[Message|MessageBox]] behind it without the ability to select any items in the inventory screen or be able to exit the inventory screen or be able to see the message in order to click the OK button. In other words, you will be stuck. #Calling 'Activate Player 1' on a stack of items will only transport a single item to the player's inventory, and destroy all other items in the stack. For this reason, it is recommended to instead use [[MoveToContainer]] to keep the stack intact. Note that this alternate method will not be considered as stealing. ##This has been fixed in [[JIP LN NVSE]] v56.08. *If an item is moved into an actor's inventory via [[Activate]], it will remain a valid reference until the cell is no longer loaded (for example, if the game session is ended).
==See Also== *[[OnActivate]] *[[IsActionRef]] *[[GetActionRef]]
[[Category:Functions (GECK)]] [[Category: Functions]] [[Category: Functions (GECK)]] [[Category: Object Functions]] [[Category:Functions (FO3)]] [[Category:Savebaked Functions]]

{{Function |origin = GECK1 |summary = Adds an achievement by index to GFWL or Steam (''New Vegas'') |name = AddAchievement |returnType = void |arguments = {{FunctionArgument |Name = AchievementNumber |Type = int }} |example = AddAchievement 12 }} == Achievements (''Fallout: New Vegas'') == {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (for base ''Fallout: New Vegas'') |- | 1 | New Kid |- | 2 | Up and Comer |- | 3 | The Boss |- | 4 | Ol' Buddy Ol' Pal |- | 5 | The Whole Gang's Here |- | 6 | Crafty |- | 7 | Mod Machine |- | 8 | Walker of the Mojave |- | 9 | Master of the Mojave |- | 10 | Globe Trotter |- | 11 | You Run Barter Town |- | 12 | Blast Mastery |- | 13 | Love the Bomb |- | 14 | Lead Dealer |- | 15 | No Tumbler Fumbler |- | 16 | Stim-ply Amazing |- | 17 | New Vegas Samurai |- | 18 | Jury Rigger |- | 19 | Hack the Mojave |- | 20 | Artful Pocketer |- | 21 | Outstanding Orator |- | 22 | Desert Survivalist |- | 23 | Old-Tyme Brawler |- | 24 | Know When to Fold Them |- | 25 | One Armed Bandit |- | 26 | Little Wheel |- | 27 | Double Down |- | 28 | Caravan Master |- | 29 | The Courier Who Broke the Bank |- | 30 | Hardcore |- | 31 | Ain't That a Kick in the Head |- | 32 | They Went That-a-Way |- | 33 | Ring-a-Ding-Ding! |- | 34 | The House Always Wins |- | 35 | For the Republic |- | 36 | Render Unto Caesar |- | 37 | Wild Card |- | 38 | All or Nothing |- | 39 | Veni, Vidi, Vici |- | 40 | Eureka! |- | 41 | No Gods, No Masters |- | 42 | Come Fly With Me |- | 43 | Talent Pool |- | 44 | Return to Sender |- | 45 | Arizona Killer |- | 46 | You'll Know It When It Happens |- | 47 | G.I. Blues |- | 48 | That Lucky Old Sun |- | 49 | Volare! |- | 50 | The Legend of the Star |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number !Achievement (''Dead Money'') |- | 51 | Assemble Your Crew |- | 52 | Cash Out |- | 53 | Having a Ball |- | 54 | Safety Deposit Box |- | 55 | Sierra Madre Souvenir Aficionado |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (''Honest Hearts'') |- | 56 | In a Foreign Land |- | 57 | May my Hand Forget its Skill |- | 58 | O Daughter of Babylon |- | 59 | Restore Our Fortunes |- | 60 | When We Remembered Zion |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (''Old World Blues'') |- | 61 | Cardiac Arrest! |- | 62 | Make up Your Mind |- | 63 | Making Friends |- | 64 | Outsmarted |- | 65 | Spinal-Tapped |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (''Lonesome Road'') |- | 66 | ED-Ecated |- | 67 | Condemned to Repeat It |- | 68 | Hometown Hero |- | 69 | Rocket's Red Glare |- | 70 | Warhead Hunter |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (''Gun Runners Arsenal'') |- | 71 | Curios and Relics |- | 72 | Master of the Arsenal |- | 73 | Up to the Challenge |- | 74 | Combat Veteran |- | 75 | Pros Only |}
== Achievements (''Fallout 3'') == {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (for base ''Fallout 3'') |- | 1 | Vault 101 Citizenship Award |- | 2 | The G.O.A.T. Whisperer |- | 3 | Escape! |- | 4 | Following in His Footsteps |- | 5 | Galaxy News Radio |- | 6 | Scientific Pursuits |- | 7 | Tranquility Lane |- | 8 | The Waters of Life |- | 9 | Picking Up the Trail |- | 10 | Rescue from Paradise |- | 11 | Finding the Garden of Eden |- | 12 | The American Dream |- | 13 | Take it Back! |- | 14 | Big Trouble in Big Town |- | 15 | The Superhuman Gambit |- | 16 | The Wasteland Survival Guide |- | 17 | Those! |- | 18 | The Nuka-Cola Challenge |- | 19 | Head of State |- | 20 | The Replicated Man |- | 21 | Blood Ties |- | 22 | Oasis |- | 23 | The Power of the Atom |- | 24 | Tenpenny Tower |- | 25 | Strictly Business |- | 26 | You Gotta Shoot 'Em in the Head |- | 27 | Stealing Independence |- | 28 | Trouble on the Homefront |- | 29 | Agatha's Song |- | 30 | Reilly's Rangers |- | 31 | Reaver |- | 32 | Mercenary |- | 33 | Protector |- | 34 | Harbinger of War |- | 35 | Pinnacle of Survival |- | 36 | Ambassador of Peace |- | 37 | Scourge of Humanity |- | 38 | Paradigm of Humanity |- | 39 | Last, Best Hope of Humanity |- | 40 | Weaponsmith |- | 41 | Doesn't Play Well with Others |- | 42 | Slayer of Beasts |- | 43 | Silver-Tongued Devil |- | 44 | Data Miner |- | 45 | Keys are for Cowards |- | 46 | One-Man Scouting Party |- | 47 | Psychotic Prankster |- | 48 | The Bigger They Are... |- | 49 | Yes, I Play with Dolls |- | 50 | Vault-Tec C.E.O. |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (''Operation: Anchorage'') |- | 51 | Aiding the Outcasts |- | 52 | Operation: Anchorage! |- | 53 | The Guns of Anchorage |- | 54 | Paving the Way |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number !Achievement (''The Pitt'') |- | 55 | Free Labor |- | 56 | Into The Pitt |- | 57 | Unsafe Working Conditions |- | 58 | Mill Worker |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (''Broken Steel'') |- | 59 | Death From Above |- | 60 | Shock Value |- | 61 | Who Dares Wins |- | 62 | Devil |- | 63 | True Mortal |- | 64 | Messiah |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (''Point Lookout'') |- | 65 | The Local Flavor |- | 66 | Walking with Spirits |- | 67 | A Meeting of the Minds |- | 68 | Bog Walker |} {| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! Achievement (''Mothership Zeta'') |- | 69 | Not of This World |- | 70 | Among the Stars |- | 71 | This Galaxy Ain't Big Enough... |- | 72 | Alien Archivist |} For information about what these achievements are, see *[https://fallout.wiki/wiki/Fallout:_New_Vegas_achievements_and_trophies Fallout: New Vegas achievements and trophies]. *[https://fallout.wiki/wiki/Fallout_3_achievements_and_trophies Fallout 3 achievements and trophies].
